Background

		Mr. Steven B. Bing, J.D., served as an Senior Vice President of Sales and Marketing at New Business and Video Services for National Rural Telecommunications Cooperative since 2005. Mr. Bing served as Senior Vice President of New Business Development at National Rural Telecommunications Cooperative. In this role, he leads a team focused on finding and developing new business opportunities to help NRTC's rural telco and electric utility members continue to deliver advanced ... telecommunications technologies. Prior to NRTC in 2005, Mr. Bing has been a Partner in a $40 million venture fund that has assisted start-up companies in a wide range of industries. From 1972 to 1984, he served as Vice President in charge of public affairs for the University of Louisville. His involvement with NRTC dates to the beginning of the DIRECTV business when he was a Partner with Direct Programming Services (DPS), an NRTC affiliate that worked with electric cooperatives throughout rural Kentucky to distribute DIRECTV service. In the mid 1990s, He also served as an Advisor to NRTC's board of directors. He served as Fund Manager of Prosperitas Investment Partners, LP. Mr. Bing served as a Principal and Chief Operating officer of Prosperities Investment Partners, LP from 1999 to 2007. From 1989 to March 1992, he served as President of ICH Corporation. From 1984 to 1989, he served as Senior Vice President of ICH Corporation. At R. Gene Smith, Inc. where he served as Vice President, he is skilled in business development, finance and analysis, strategic planning, acquisitions/mergers, operations and marketing/public relations. He has enjoyed a successful career as an Entrepreneur and business leader. His current and past business board activity is extensive for both business and civic/charitable activities. Mr. Bing has held senior positions with the Kentucky governor's office where, he served as a Senior Budget and Policy Analyst, at the University of Louisville where he served as Vice President for University Relations. He has been a Director of Almost Family Inc. since January 1992. He serves as a Director of Zefcom, LLC. He served as a Director of Antisoma Inc. (also Known as Aptamera, Inc.) and DermTech International. Mr. Bing received BA in political science from the University of Kentucky and a JD (cum laude) from the University of Louisville.Read Full Background




